<h2>Style-Specific Considerations</h2>

<h3>Belt Colour Variations</h3>

<p>While the kyu-dan structure remains consistent, colours differ. Shotokan traditionally uses white, yellow, orange, green, purple, brown, and black. Other styles may include additional colours or different sequences. Software should allow custom colour configuration for each rank.</p>

<h3>Organisation Requirements</h3>

<p>Many karate schools affiliate with larger organisations (JKA, SKA, WKF, etc.) that impose specific testing requirements, registration processes, and rank recognition. Software should track organisation membership and support their administrative requirements.</p>

