<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>What is karate school software?</h3>

<p>Karate school software is a management platform designed specifically for karate dojos. It handles student databases, kyu-dan belt progression, kata curriculum tracking, class scheduling, testing management, and billing while using karate-appropriate terminology and workflows.</p>

<h3>Can karate software track kata progress?</h3>

<p>Yes, quality karate software includes kata library management. You can track which kata students have learned, which they are currently studying, and which are required for their next belt. Some systems link video resources for reference and allow performance notes.</p>

<h3>How does belt testing work in karate software?</h3>

<p>The system tracks attendance and time-in-rank to determine testing eligibility automatically. When students qualify, they can register and pay testing fees. After the test, results are recorded and ranks update automatically, triggering certificate generation and belt ordering workflows.</p>

<h3>Does karate software support different styles?</h3>

<p>Yes, configurable systems support various styles (Shotokan, Goju-Ryu, Shito-Ryu, Wado-Ryu, etc.) with custom belt colours, kata lists, and testing requirements specific to each style traditions. You can even manage multiple styles within the same dojo.</p>

<h3>Can parents manage children accounts?</h3>

<p>Yes, family accounts allow parents to manage multiple children from a single login. They can view schedules, track belt progress for each child, make payments, receive communications about their children training, and access progress reports.</p>

<h3>How much does karate school software cost?</h3>

<p>Most karate software costs 50-150 GBP per month depending on student count and features. Smaller schools typically find options at 50-80 GBP monthly. Pricing often scales with active student numbers or follows tiered plans based on features.</p>

<h3>Can I try karate software before committing?</h3>

<p>Most karate school software providers offer free trials ranging from 14 to 30 days. This allows you to test the features with your actual data, train your staff, and evaluate how well the platform fits your dojo operations before making a financial commitment.</p>

